docs.abstract: The Government Accountability Office found that black students still bear the brunt of school discipline, undermining Trump administration efforts to re-examine Obama-era policies.
docs.snippet: The Government Accountability Office found that black students still bear the brunt of school discipline, undermining Trump administration efforts to re-examine Obama-era policies.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Black students continue to be disciplined at school more often and more harshly than their white peers, often for similar infractions, according to a new report by Congress’s nonpartisan watchdog agency, which counters claims fueling the Trump administration’s efforts to re-examine discipline policies of the Obama administration.

headline.main: Government Watchdog Finds Racial Bias in School Discipline
headline.print_headline: National Analysis Sees Bias in Discipline

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Paul D. Ryan, a fierce believer in America as a land of immigrants, recently attended a dinner party with a so-called Dreamer. docs.abstract: Larry Kudlow's predictions, which will soon carry new weight as the president’s top economic adviser, have not always been on the mark. The following is a look back at some of his economic predictions that did not bear out.

docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump has a new chief economic adviser. Larry Kudlow, the CNBC commentator who served in President Ronald Reagan’s Office of Management and Budget, will become the director of the National Economic Council, a position being vacated by Gary D. Cohn, who said he would resign after losing an internal battle over the president’s plan to impose tariffs on foreign metals.
